BoundAttributes.Name: OverscanCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that determines how many additional items will be rendered
            before and after the visible region. This help to reduce the frequency of rendering
            during scrolling. However, higher values mean that more elements will be present
            in the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SpacerElement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or sets the tag name of the HTML element that will be used as the virtualization spacer.
             One such element will be rendered before the visible items, and one more after them, using
             an explicit "height" style to control the scroll range.
            
             The default value is "div". If you are placing the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1" /> instance inside
             an element that requires a specific child tag name, consider setting that here. For example when
             rendering inside a "tbody", consider setting <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1.SpacerElement" /> to the value "tr".
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

BoundAttributes.Name: Anchor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML ID of the anchor element this region is positioned relative to
            This must be set for the component positioning logic to be active.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Viewport
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The HTML ID of the viewport element this region is positioned relative to
            If unset the parent element of the anchored region is used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalPositioningMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets what logic the component uses to determine horizontal placement.
            Locktodefault forces the default position
            Dynamic decides placement based on available space
            Uncontrolled (default) does not control placement on the horizontal axis
            See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.AxisPositioningMode" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalDefaultPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The default horizontal position of the region relative to the anchor element
            Default is unset. See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.HorizontalPosition" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalViewportLock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the region remains in the viewport (ie. detaches from the anchor) on the horizontal axis
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalInset
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the region overlaps the anchor on the horizontal axis. Default is false which places the region adjacent to the anchor element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalThreshold
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            How narrow the space allocated to the default position has to be before the widest area
            is selected for layout
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalScaling
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how the width of the region is calculated
            Default is "Content". See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.AxisScalingMode" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalPositioningMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets what logic the component uses to determine vertical placement.
            Locktodefault forces the default position
            Dynamic decides placement based on available space
            Uncontrolled (default) does not control placement on the vertical axis
            See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.AxisPositioningMode" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalDefaultPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The default vertical position of the region relative to the anchor element
            Default is "Unset".See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.VerticalPosition" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalViewportLock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the region remains in the viewport (ie. detaches from the anchor) on the vertical axis
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalInset
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the region overlaps the anchor on the vertical axis
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalThreshold
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            How short the space allocated to the default position has to be before the tallest area
            is selected for layout
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VerticalScaling
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines how the height of the region is calculated
            Default is "Content". See <seealso cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.AxisScalingMode" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FixedPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the region is positioned using css "position: fixed".
            Otherwise the region uses "position: absolute".
            Fixed placement allows the region to break out of parent containers,
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoUpdateMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines what triggers the anchored region to revaluate positioning
            Default is "Anchor". In 'anchor' mode only anchor resizes and attribute changes will provoke an update. In 'auto' mode the component also updates because of - any scroll event on the document, window resizes and viewport resizes. See <seealso cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentAnchoredRegion.AutoUpdateMode" />
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.PropertyColumn<TGridItem, TValue>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents a <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1" /> column whose cells display a single value.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TGridItem">The type of data represented by each row in the grid.</typeparam>
            <typeparam name="TValue">The type of the value being displayed in the column's cells.</typeparam>

BoundAttributes.Name: TGridItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TGridItem for the Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.PropertyColumn<TGridItem, TValue> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: TValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TValue for the Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.PropertyColumn<TGridItem, TValue> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: Property
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the value to be displayed in this column's cells.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Optionally specifies a format string for the value.
            
             Using this requires the <typeparamref name="TValue" /> type to implement <see cref="T:System.IFormattable" />.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Comparer
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optionally specifies how to compare values in this column when sorting.
            
            Using this requires the <typeparamref name="TValue" /> type to implement <see cref="T:System.IComparable`1" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Title text for the column. This is rendered automatically if <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.ColumnBase`1.HeaderCellItemTemplate" /> is not used.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An optional CSS class name. If specified, this is included in the class attribute of table header and body cells
            for this column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Align
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If specified, controls the justification of table header and body cells for this column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderCellItemTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An optional template for this column's header cell. If not specified, the default header template
            includes the <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.ColumnBase`1.Title" /> along with any applicable sort indicators and options buttons.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColumnOptions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If specified, indicates that this column has this associated options UI. A button to display this
             UI will be included in the header cell by default.
            
             If <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.ColumnBase`1.HeaderCellItemTemplate" /> is used, it is left up to that template to render any relevant
             "show options" UI and invoke the grid's <see cref="M:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.ShowColumnOptions(Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.ColumnBase{`0})" />).
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Sortable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Indicates whether the data should be sortable by this column.
            
             The default value may vary according to the column type (for example, a <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.TemplateColumn`1" />
             is sortable by default if any <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.TemplateColumn`1.SortBy" /> parameter is specified).
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsDefaultSort
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If specified and not null, indicates that this column represents the initial sort order
            for the grid. The supplied value controls the default sort direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PlaceholderTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If specified, virtualized grids will use this template to render cells whose data has not yet been loaded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid<TGridItem>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            A component that displays a grid.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TGridItem">The type of data represented by each row in the grid.</typeparam>

BoundAttributes.Name: TGridItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TGridItem for the Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid<TGridItem> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             A queryable source of data for the grid.
            
             This could be in-memory data converted to queryable using the
             <see cref="M:System.Linq.Queryable.AsQueryable(System.Collections.IEnumerable)" /> extension method,
             or an EntityFramework DataSet or an <see cref="T:System.Linq.IQueryable" /> derived from it.
            
             You should supply either <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.RowsData" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.RowsDataProvider" />, but not both.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsDataProvider
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             A callback that supplies data for the rid.
            
             You should supply either <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.RowsData" /> or <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.RowsDataProvider" />, but not both.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the child components of this instance. For example, you may define columns by adding
            components derived from the <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.ColumnBase`1" /> base class.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Virtualize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If true, the grid will be rendered with virtualization. This is normally used in conjunction with
             scrolling and causes the grid to fetch and render only the data around the current scroll viewport.
             This can greatly improve the performance when scrolling through large data sets.
            
             If you use <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.Virtualize" />, you should supply a value for <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.RowsDataSize" /> and must
             ensure that every row renders with the same constant height.
            
             Generally it's preferable not to use <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.Virtualize" /> if the amount of data being rendered
             is small or if you are using pagination.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsDataSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            This is applicable only when using <see cref="P:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1.Virtualize" />. It defines an expected height in pixels for
            each row, allowing the virtualization mechanism to fetch the correct number of items to match the display
            size and to ensure accurate scrolling.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ResizableColumns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If true, renders draggable handles around the column headers, allowing the user to resize the columns
            manually. Size changes are not persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowsDataKey
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Optionally defines a value for @key on each rendered row. Typically this should be used to specify a
             unique identifier, such as a primary key value, for each data item.
            
             This allows the grid to preserve the association between row elements and data items based on their
             unique identifiers, even when the <typeparamref name="TGridItem" /> instances are replaced by new copies (for
             example, after a new query against the underlying data store).
            
             If not set, the @key will be the <typeparamref name="TGridItem" /> instance itself.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Pagination
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Optionally links this <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentDataGrid`1" /> instance with a <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.PaginationState" /> model,
             causing the grid to fetch and render only the current page of data.
            
             This is normally used in conjunction with a <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.FluentPaginator" /> component or some other UI logic
             that displays and updates the supplied <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.PaginationState" /> instance.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NoTabbing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true the component will not add itself to the tab queue. Default is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GenerateHeader
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Whether the grid should automatically generate a header row and its type
            See <see cref="T:Microsoft.Fast.Components.FluentUI.GenerateHeaderOption" />
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GridTemplateColumns
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the value that gets applied to the css gridTemplateColumns attribute of child rows
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRowFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback when a row is focused
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnCellFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback when a row is focused
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RowClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optionally defines a class to be applied to a rendered row. 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Class
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional CSS class names. If given, these will be included in the class attribute of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Style
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Optional in-line styles. If given, these will be included in the style attribute of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BackReference
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A reference to the enclosing component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdditionalAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a collection of additional attributes that will be applied to the created element.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...

For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture

BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for binding the value to the attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for updating the bound value when a new value is available.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: after
